Capture the timeoutId in a closure.<p><pre><code>  $(document).ready((function() {
    $(&#x27;input&#x27;).keypress((function() {
        var timeoutId = null;

        return function() {
            window.clearTimeout(timeoutId);
            timeoutId = window.setTimeout(function() {
                $.ajax({ /* ... * /});
            }, 200);
        };
    })());
  });

  // NB: this solution only works if there is one input.
  // If there are more than one, you need to create a new closure for each one.</code></pre>
